---
description: General thesis project rules
alwaysApply: true
---

This is a thesis web application for reporting public lighting faults in Košice.

Implement the application from scratch.
Do not use code from previous student projects.

The system is not a full local report lifecycle management system.
It is a map and integration layer for the existing DPMK/AUSEMIO reporting process.

The application must help the citizen select a street light or location on a map and prepare data for the existing DPMK/AUSEMIO form.

Do not implement local technician workflows, operator roles, repair status management, report history management, or a local authoritative report database.

Keep frontend, backend, and database separated.

Keep code simple, readable, typed where possible, and ready for future development.

When adding new functionality, check whether it fits the thesis scope. If it creates a parallel reporting system, do not implement it.
